\begin{defini}
\label{def-KreinColl}
Given a norm continuous path $t\in[-1,1]\mapsto T_t$ of ${J} $-unitaries, two continuous paths $t\in[-1,1]\mapsto \lambda_{1,2}(t)$ of discrete eigenvalues of $T_t$ undergo a Krein collision at $t=0$ if $\lambda_{1,2}(t)\in{\mathbb S}^1$ for $t\in(-1,0]$ and $\lambda_{1,2}(t)\not\in{\mathbb S}^1$ for $t\in(0,1]$, see Figure~\ref{fig-KreinColl}. Similarly, Krein collisions for paths of real discrete eigenvalues of ${J} $-hermitian operators are defined.
