\begin{coro}
\label{coro-AtiyahSinger}
Suppose the same hypothesis as in Theorem~\ref{theo-connectedReal}. The set of ${\mathbb F}{\mathbb H}({\cal K},{J},{S})$ has the following deformation retracts:

\begin{enumerate}[\rm (i)]

\item the set of real Fredholm operators for $({\eta},{\tau})=(1,1)$;

\item the set of anti-symmetric Fredholm operators for $({\eta},{\tau})=(-1,-1)$;

\item the set of quaternionic Fredholm operators for $({\eta},{\tau})=(-1,1)$;

\item the set of symmetric Fredholm operators for $({\eta},{\tau})=(1,-1)$.

\end{enumerate}

These sets are respectively the classifying spaces ${\mathbb F}_0$, ${\mathbb F}_2$, ${\mathbb F}_4$ and ${\mathbb F}_6$ for Real $K$-theory of Atiyah and Singer \cite{AS}.

\end{coro}


